{{Infobox organization |name= Jewish People Policy Institute | image = המכון למדיניות העם היהודי - ירושלים 1.jpg | image_size = 350px | caption = The sign of the institute on its building at Jerusalem's [[Rehavia|Rehavia neighborhood]] |type= |founded_date = {{start date and age|2002}} |headquarters = [[Jerusalem, Israel]] |website = [http://www.jppi.org.il/ jppi.org.il] }}
'''The Jewish People Policy Institute''' ('''JPPI'''; {{lang-he|המכון למדיניות העם היהודי}}; formerly: '''The Jewish People Policy Planning (JPPPI)'''), is a [[Non-profit organization]] with the purpose of promoting and securing the [[Jew|Jewish people]] and [[Israel]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Jewish People Policy Institute|url=http://www.thejewishweek.com/jewish_people_policy_institute|publisher=NY-The Jewish Week|accessdate=16 November 2013}}</ref> The institute is a professional policy planning apparatus and a strategic thought process for the Jewish people in the most fundamental subjects concerning the Jewish people. The institute is served by most prominent public figures from the government, academia, the private sector in Israel and Jewish communities around the world, who constitute the [[think tank]] of this body.
The JPPI's viewpoint is all-Jewish and long term, and a cornerstone of its work is the premise that Israel is the core of the Jewish people. Its think tank systematically and professionally examines the challenges, threats and opportunities that the Jewish people are coping with, and develops principles for policies and strategic alternatives. In addition, it may recommend on immediate steps needed to be taken in order to secure the continuity and prosperity of the Jewish people.
JPPI was founded in 2002 by the [[Jewish Agency for Israel]], and is run as an independent body. It is headed by a board of directors that is now chaired by [[Dennis Ross]], the special advisor for the Persian Gulf Southwest Asia in U.S. President [[Barack Obama]]'s administration. Its current President is Avinoam Bar-Yosef.<ref>{{cite news|title=Conference to discuss Jewish world's budget|url=http://www.ynetnews.com/articles/0,7340,L-4296104,00.html|accessdate=16 November 2013|newspaper=[[Ynet]]}}</ref>
==External links== {{Commons-inline|Category:The Jewish People Policy Institute|The Jewish People Policy Institute}} *[http://www.jppi.org.il/ JPPI's official website] *[http://www.jewishagency.org The Jewish Agency for Israel] *[http://www.timesofisrael.com/topic/jppi-jewish-people-policy-institute/ JPPI related articles] on [[The Times of Israel]] *[http://ejewishphilanthropy.com/conference-on-the-future-of-the-jewish-people/ Conference on the Future of the Jewish People] * [http://www.jpost.com/Breaking-News/Hackers-attack-Jewish-People-Policy-Institute-site Hackers attack Jewish People Policy Institute site] on [[Jpost]]
